{
  "stem": "9590.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And at night, the Russian army occupied our territory.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But Froiko was very injured.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A lot-- he lost a lot of blood.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that morning, the following morning, we went to Rowne, to a hospital.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He was operated, but he didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He died, after a few days in Rowne.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "For us to come to Rowne and see how the city is empty of Jews-- when we walked from the hospital all the way up where we lived, where we went to school, where we had so much fun, and saw the emptiness, the devastating environment, I think that was the hardest thing for us to accept.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I cried all the way from the hospital, till we went where-- where we lived in the Jewish quarters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "We were very disappointed, very, very disappointed.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Then, we found some Jews that were also hidden.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And somehow, we had something in-- in common.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We asked who survived, and who didn't, and what happened, and what.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we-- we felt that we are part of each other.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We could not let go, our feelings.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "There was still a lot of surviving to do.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The fact that my-- that Froiko died was a terrible blow for us, terrible.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "He suffered so much through the-- the whole war.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "He went through so much agony-- and we had lived already to see the liberation-- and didn't make it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "He was buried in Rowne.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But the war was still on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And we were afraid that the Germans will retreat.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So we went further down to Russia.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "We went to Volodymyr-Volynskyl, and settled there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "We stayed there for a few weeks, till the Russian army went forward and forward.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And they were already in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then they were already in Germany, so we came back to Rowne.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
